00:37:14.010 --> 00:37:17.730
So just to sum up, I
haven't written a book.

00:37:17.730 --> 00:37:19.830
I tried to come up with
some memorable acronym.

00:37:19.830 --> 00:37:21.720
And I'm not sure
that I've succeeded.

00:37:21.720 --> 00:37:25.770
But I was thinking harness
the power of sleep.

00:37:25.770 --> 00:37:30.080
So P is for planning ahead,
prioritizing that seven hours.

00:37:30.080 --> 00:37:34.050
O is for getting outdoors
as much as possible.

00:37:34.050 --> 00:37:37.210
W is protecting that
wind down routine.

00:37:37.210 --> 00:37:39.570
Whether you have 30
minutes or 60 minutes,

00:37:39.570 --> 00:37:44.160
make that time work for
you in unwinding for sleep.

00:37:44.160 --> 00:37:45.690
E is for energizing.

00:37:45.690 --> 00:37:47.890
You still want to energize
your body during the day.

00:37:47.890 --> 00:37:50.280
But do it as
naturally as you can.

00:37:50.280 --> 00:37:52.260
And think about
limiting your caffeine,

00:37:52.260 --> 00:37:56.080
switching out caffeine for
decaf where it makes sense.

00:37:56.080 --> 00:37:57.600
And finally, R--

00:37:57.600 --> 00:37:59.280
I've said this a
lot of times today--

00:37:59.280 --> 00:38:01.320
routine, routine, routine.

00:38:01.320 --> 00:38:03.570
That's really going to
help your body clock.

00:38:03.570 --> 00:38:07.230
And set reminders on your
phone, remind other people

00:38:07.230 --> 00:38:09.540
in your family that actually
you're going to try this

00:38:09.540 --> 00:38:13.750
and commit to it because it
will be better for all of you.

